line_1: To rocky Beds, and cranny'd Jettings clung.
line_2: Oysters around on cliffy Peaks are hung,

line_1: The favouring winds around the virgin clung,
line_2: Nor was the daring Clusia then unsung,

line_1: Beneath, the Children round their Mother clung;
line_2: High in the Boughs the murder'd Father hung;

line_1: While round my knees they fondly clung;
line_2: To hear them lisp their mothers tongue.

line_1: With many an untaught beauty clung,
Robb'd of the prop, where once she fondly clung,
line_2: The faded woodbine trails the earth along;

line_1: Whilst round my knees they fondly clung,
line_2: To hear 'em lisp their mother's tongue.

line_1: Whose slimy Waters to its Arches clung,
line_2: Where wrap'd in Weeds the clodded Vermin hung,

line_1: Still as he flew, around him sportive clung
line_2: Wafting the fragrance which his tresses flung:

line_1: Or round Humility the languor clung!
line_2: Whether from Pride the malady first sprung,

line_1: Around her neck as in despair they clung;
line_2: By malice urged, by ruthless envy stung,
As round the bleeding neck he hung.
